see Doc/books.texinfo for more/old/alternate info

Books is compiled from source

On Windows

Cygwin for make, bash, subversion
       http://cygwin.com/setup.exe

GNAT GPL 2012 for Ada, GtkAda
     http://libre.adacore.com/download/configurations
     gnat-gpl-2012-i686-pc-mingw32-bin.exe
     gtkada-gpl-2.24.2-nt.exe

     install gtkada to same directory as gnat
     
gnade for odbc binding
      using gnade_1.6.2.orig.tar.gz from Debian gnade package

      cd /Projects
      tar zxf gnade_1.6.2.orig.tar.gz
      cd gnade-1.6.2.orig
      ./configure
      mkdir -p lib-obj/Debug
      cd dbi/odbc
      make prep

mysql
    http://www.mysql.com/downloads/ Community Server
    mysql-installer-5.5.25a.0.msi
        don't install workbench; it requires MS stuff
        install all of server, just ODBC connector (simplifies uninstall later)
        configure as Developer machine
        set db admin password

Create database
    edit /books/src/create_user_mysql.sql to specify you
    
    run MySQL command line client
    source /books/src/create_database_books_mysql.sql
    source /books/src/create_user_mysql.sql;
    source /books/src/create_schema_mysql.sql;
    quit;
    
create ODBC data source
    Control Panel | Administrative Tools | Data Source (ODBC) | User DSN tab | Add
    Data Source Name : books
    Host/Server Name : localhost
    Database Name : books

    click Test; fix any problems
    
compile
    cd books/build/x86_gnu_windows/release
    edit makefile to set ADA_PROJECT_PATH
    make all

to restore database from SQL backup:
   run mysql command line client
   source <file.sql>;
   doesn't like network drives, spaces in file names
        
